# SignalSynth — Project Rules for Cascade

## What This Project Is
SignalSynth is an AI-powered market intelligence system for eBay's Collectibles & Trading Cards business. It scrapes 42+ sources, enriches posts into actionable insights, clusters them into strategic themes, and provides an AI-driven "Ask AI" analysis layer with adaptive response formatting.

## Architecture
```
Scrapers (utils/scrape_*.py)
  → Raw posts (data/*.json)
    → Enrichment pipeline (quick_process.py)
      → precomputed_insights.json (9,000+ insights)
        → Clustering (precompute_clusters.py)
          → precomputed_clusters.json (21 themes)
            → Streamlit dashboard (app.py)
              → Ask AI (GPT-4.1 with adaptive formatting)
              → Strategy tab (cluster cards + doc generation)
              → Competitor/Customer/Industry tabs
```

## Key Files
- **app.py** — Main Streamlit app. Contains Ask AI logic, KPI banner, all tabs, retrieval scoring, adaptive format templates, system prompt. ~3700 lines.
- **quick_process.py** — Enrichment pipeline. Loads all scraped data, applies relevance filters, enriches with taxonomy/sentiment/persona/churn/signal-strength, saves precomputed_insights.json. Also does delta detection (snapshot comparison).
- **precompute_clusters.py** — Clusters insights into strategic themes using DBSCAN + GPT summarization. Saves precomputed_clusters.json.
- **components/cluster_synthesizer.py** — Core clustering logic: workstream assignment, keyword matching, quote selection, GPT metadata generation.
- **components/cluster_view_simple.py** — Streamlit UI for cluster cards in Strategy tab. Has document generation (PRD/BRD/PRFAQ/Jira).
- **components/hybrid_retrieval.py** — BM25 + dense embedding retrieval with RRF merge for Ask AI.
- **components/signal_scorer.py** — Semantic + heuristic signal strength scoring using e5-base-v2 embeddings.
- **utils/scrape_all.py** — Master scraper orchestrator. Calls all individual scrapers.
- **utils/scrape_reddit.py** — Reddit scraper (public JSON API, 47 subreddits, 88 search queries).
- **utils/scrape_competitors.py** — Competitor & subsidiary scraper (Whatnot, Heritage, Fanatics, Goldin, TCGPlayer, etc.).
- **ai_training_feedback.json** — Thumbs up/down feedback from Ask AI responses.

## Domain Knowledge (CRITICAL)
- **eBay SUBSIDIARIES** (owned by eBay, NOT competitors): Goldin (premium auctions), TCGPlayer (TCG marketplace)
- **eBay PARTNERSHIPS**: PSA (vault, consignment, grading), Card Ladder (receives eBay transaction data for indexes)
- **TRUE COMPETITORS**: Whatnot (live breaks), Fanatics Collect (marketplace + Topps/Panini), Heritage Auctions (high-end), Beckett (grading, acquired by Fanatics), Vinted (resale), Alt (fractional), COMC (consignment)
- **eBay Products**: Vault, Authenticity Guarantee (AG), Price Guide, eBay Live, Promoted Listings, Seller Hub, Managed Payments
- **Price Guide Strategy**: eBay provides transaction data TO Card Ladder/PSA (not the reverse). eBay's goal is to be THE premier price guide.
- **User Personas**: Power Seller, Collector, Investor, New Seller, Casual Buyer

