## Data Pipeline Commands
```
# Full refresh (scrape + process + cluster + push):
python utils/scrape_all.py
python quick_process.py
python precompute_clusters.py
git add -A; git commit -m "data refresh"; git push

# Quick reprocess (no scraping, just re-enrich and recluster):
python quick_process.py
python precompute_clusters.py
```

## Ask AI Architecture
- 11 question-type detectors: briefing, competitive, subsidiary, product, fees, persona, comparison, review, trend, liquidity, broad
- Each type has an adaptive format template with specific sections/tables
- Retrieval: hybrid (BM25 + embeddings) with source diversity cap
- Context includes: retrieved signals, aggregate stats, cluster themes, trend alerts, delta detection, competitor landscape, industry news, triangulation
- Follow-up question suggestions generated via gpt-4o-mini after each response
- Multi-turn conversation memory (last 2 exchanges)

## Common Issues
- "whatnot" matches the English word — use "whatnot app", "whatnot live", etc. in keyword lists
- "PSA" matches "public service announcement" on Reddit — require grading context
- NOISE_SUBREDDITS blocklist in quick_process.py filters gaming/sports/relationship subs
- Streamlit Cloud sleeps free-tier apps — GitHub Actions cron (.github/workflows/keep-alive.yml) pings every 25 min
- Cluster quotes can be irrelevant if fallback is too loose — synthesize_cluster() in cluster_synthesizer.py has dedup + topicality checks
- Promotional content filter in app.py normalize_insight() marks _is_promotional posts
